    <article xml:id="features">
        <title>An article showcasing differents features of STACK questions in PreText</title>

        <frontmatter>

            <bibinfo>
                <author>
                    <personname>Chris Sangwin</personname>
                    <institution>University of Edinburgh</institution>
                </author>
                <date><today /></date>
            </bibinfo>

            <abstract>
                <p>This is an article serving as a test suite for various STACK features in PreTeXt.</p>
            </abstract>

        </frontmatter>

        <introduction>
                <p>This is an article serving as a test suite for various STACK features in PreTeXt.</p>
        </introduction>

        <section xml:id="section-stack">
            <title>STACK questions</title>
            <introduction>
                <p>The following illustrates various features of STACK questions.</p>

                <p>These serve as test cases.</p>

                <!-- <image xml:id="my-image">
                    <latex-image label="my-latex-image">
                        \begin{tikzpicture}[scale=2.4]
                            \node[circle, draw] {Circle};
                        \end{tikzpicture}
                    </latex-image>
                </image> -->

                <p>
                    Issues:
                    <ol>
                        <li>
                            <p>Adapt/adapt-delay block: Currently not supported.</p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p>Validation-state-listener: Currently not supported - An Error occured while processing the question (In API, the error is: Unknown message-type: "track-validation-state")</p>
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </p>
            </introduction>
            
            <subsection xml:id="subsec-formats">
                <title>Inclusion formats</title>
                <p>STACK questions can be included in Moodle XML format or (as of STACK 4.11) YAML format.</p>

                <exercises xml:id="exercises-xml-yaml">
                    <exercise xml:id="ex-integration-xml">
                        <title>Question in XML format</title>
                        <stack label="stk-integration-xml" source="stack/01_integration_with_feedback.xml" />
                    </exercise>
                    
                    <exercise xml:id="ex-integration-yaml">
                        <title>Question in YAML format</title>
                        <stack label="stk-integration-yaml" source="stack/01_integration_with_feedback.yaml" />
                    </exercise>
                </exercises>

                <exercise xml:id="ex-integration-knowl">
                    <title>Question in a knowl</title>
                    <stack label="stk-integration-knowl" source="stack/01_integration_with_feedback.xml" />
                </exercise>

            </subsection>

